        <div class="race"><a id="race">Race</a></div>
        <div class="Race1">
            Race is an event type in Need for Speed: Heat, made up of either multiple lap circuits or single point-to-point sprints, 
            and take place on roads. The first racer to cross the finish line after completing all laps or reaching the end point of 
            a sprint first is the winner. <br><br>

            Every route has multiple checkpoints that racers must pass through in order and they all have a recommended road-grip handling 
            profile.<br><br>

            An event can take place during the day or at night: <br><br>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Day - Players earn bank (Bank) from participating in events hosted by the Speedhunters Showdown and police will not get involved.
                </li> 
                <li>
                    Night - Players earn rep (Rep) from participating in illicit street racing events and engaging with the PCPD.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="drift"><a id="drift">Drift</a></div>
        <div class="drift1">
            Drift Trial is an event type in Need for Speed: Heat, made up of either multiple lap circuits or single point-to-point sprints, 
            and take place on roads. <br><br>

            The player has to beat a score target before they complete all laps of a circuit or reach the end of a point-to-point sprint. <br><br>

            Every route has multiple checkpoints that players must pass through in order and they all have a recommended road-drift handling 
            profile. <br><br>

            An event can take place during the day or at night: <br><br>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Day - Players earn bank (Bank) from participating in events hosted by the Speedhunters Showdown and police will not get involved.
                </li> 
                <li>
                    Night - Players earn rep (Rep) from participating in illicit street racing events and engaging with the PCPD.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

